Take long documents and generate a concise summary.

Examples of documetns could be: Clinical notes, Research papers, Meeting notes even email

Workflow:

Get Word/PDF/Text  
        ↓
Load Document
        ↓
Send text to LLM
        ↓
Receive summary
        ↓
Save summary

In Python, you can use Jupyterlab, install the Libraries


#############################################################################
pip install transformers torch
#############################################################################


################################################################################

from transformers import pipeline

summarizer = pipeline(
    "summarization",
    model="facebook/bart-large-cnn"
)

text = """
Artificial Intelligence has become one of the fastest growing
technologies in healthcare...
"""

summary = summarizer(
    text,
    max_length=100,
    min_length=30,
    do_sample=False
)

print(summary[0]['summary_text'])

